<div class="section_title">Exhibitor Workshop: Preview of a Successful Show</div>
<span class="text">
CES extends enormous thanks to the more than 50 exhibitors who attended the third annual International CES Exhibitor Workshop on September 21 at the Las Vegas Convention Center. They’re now armed with essential exhibitor tools to enhance their CES experience.
<P>In an information download, International CES staff from sales, marketing, communications and operations presented detailed show information, including this year’s attendee marketing campaign, the ins-and-outs of booth set up and extensive PR/marketing tips. </P>
<P>Workshop attendees also learned exhibiting tips and best practices from representative of GES Exposition Services, Smart City and Las Vegas Convention Center Security. During lunch, exhibitor attendees participated in roundtable discussions on key topics and took advantage of one-on-one dialogues with official service suppliers at a Vendor Trade Fair.&nbsp; </P>
<P>One exhibitor described the vendor fair, especially helpful to first-time exhibitors, as a “living exhibitor manual.” </P>
<P>Exhibitors also posed questions to an expert exhibitor panel, to learn more about topics such as cost-cutting tips and drawing attendees to your booth. They finished the day with a tour of the Las Vegas Convention Center.</P>Did you miss the workshop but want more information? Please contact Andrew Bradley at <A href="mailto:abradley@CE.org">abradley@CE.org</A>.
</span>
<a name="1984"></a>
