<div class="section_title">Exclusive Pre-show Exhibitor On-site Press Event</div>
<span class="text">
<IMG height=54 src="/print/images/promotions/CESUnveiled.gif" width=275> 
<P>Put your product and company name in front of <STRONG>more than 475 members of the press from 36 countries</STRONG> at an intimate International CES press event—right at the Las Vegas Convention Center. </P>
<P>Only credentialed media and market analysts are invited to attend the exclusive CEA-sponsored event <STRONG>CES Unveiled: The Official Press Event of the International CES</STRONG>, 4-7 p.m. Tuesday, January 4, 2005,&nbsp;Las Vegas Convention Center, Room S226. </P>
<P>The power of the press at International CES is huge. CES attracts more than 4,000 press representatives and over 1,500 financial/market analysts from more than 45 countries, representing print, on-line/wire and broadcast press. </P>
<P>The timing of <STRONG>CES Unveiled </STRONG>on Tuesday evening will not conflict with keynote addresses or other important events. The event will be held next to the International CES Press Room, where the press will register, convene to use the business facilities and stop for a snack. </P>
<P>The press is eager to attend <STRONG>CES Unveiled</STRONG>. More than 475 press members have <EM>already </EM>made their reservations. Make sure they see you there! Meet press representatives from CBS, CNET, <EM>Consumer Reports</EM>, <EM>Financial Times</EM>, IEEE Spectrum, <EM>Investor's Business Daily</EM>, <EM>Money Magazine</EM>, <EM>The New York Times</EM>, <EM>Sports Illustrated</EM>, <EM>The Wall Street Journal</EM>, <EM>Wired Magazine </EM>and more. </P><EM><STRONG>NEW!</STRONG></EM>&nbsp; The Innovations 2005 Design and Engineering honorees will be showcased at <STRONG>CES Unveiled</STRONG>. No other event will give the press and financial/market analysts an exclusive look at the Best of Innovations 2005 displays from this prestigious awards program. Reserve your space now at the most effective press event of the entire 2005 International CES. To reach this important group, immediately contact Ryan Strowger, Manager, Business Development, CEA at <A href="mailto:rstrowger@CE.org">rstrowger@CE.org</A> or (703) 907-7679.
</span>
